22:49.802 --> 22:50.769 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thank you.

22:50.803 --> 22:51.971 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PHILIP GORDON: Thank you.

22:52.004 --> 22:53.906 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BORIS EPSHTEYN: Thanks.

22:53.939 --> 22:59.144 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we turn now
from foreign
policy to an issue that
continues to grab

22:59.178 --> 23:05.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
headlines in the campaign:
Donald Trump's
taxes and so far his refusal to
make them

23:05.551 --> 23:07.386 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
public.

23:07.419 --> 23:11.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hillary Clinton says he must be
hiding something,
while Trump himself has pledged
to release

23:11.090 --> 23:14.627 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
them, but only when IRS is
finished its audits.

23:14.660 --> 23:17.930 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That is something that can last
seven years.

23:17.963 --> 23:19.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We want to get past all these
headlines.

23:19.999 --> 23:23.302 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And our Lisa Desjardins helps
put it all in
context.

23:23.335 --> 23:26.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Let's start
with basic facts.

23:26.205 --> 23:31.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So far, Donald Trump has not
made his tax
returns or summaries on them
public.

23:31.043 --> 23:32.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he gives a consistent
explanation.

23:32.711 --> 23:34.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP (R), Presidential
Candidate:
And I am under audit, a routine
audit.

23:34.880 --> 23:37.249 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when the audit is complete,
I will release
my returns.

23:37.283 --> 23:38.517 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know when that is going
to be.

23:38.550 --> 23:40.486 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But when the audit is complete,
I will release
my returns.

23:40.519 --> 23:41.620 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have no problem with it.

23:41.654 --> 23:42.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It doesn't matter.

23:42.655 --> 23:44.623 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But this is his
choice.

23:44.657 --> 23:49.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The IRS confirmed this year that
nothing prevents
Trump, or any of us, from
releasing personal

23:49.461 --> 23:51.363 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
tax returns anytime.

23:51.397 --> 23:56.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, most of us don't have the
1,000-page
tower of returns that Trump
tweeted about

23:56.735 --> 23:59.004 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
last year, but that's important.

23:59.038 --> 24:04.043 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You see, Trump's personal taxes
are also the
taxes of his company.

24:04.076 --> 24:10.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Trump Organization, with its
500 associated
companies, files as a kind of
family business,

24:10.115 --> 24:15.854 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
whose dealings are taxed as
Trump's personal
income, which brings us to the
bigger point:

24:15.888 --> 24:18.324 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What could Trump's taxes tell
us?

24:18.357 --> 24:20.225 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
A lot.

24:20.259 --> 24:24.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How successful the businessman
actually is,
what ties does he have abroad,
how his companies

24:24.496 --> 24:30.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
operate there, if and how much
he gives to
charity, and whether Trump pays
any taxes

24:30.269 --> 24:31.337 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
at all.

24:31.370 --> 24:32.571 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Trump likes to bring that up
himself.

24:32.604 --> 24:35.140 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I pay as little as
possible.

24:35.174 --> 24:39.044 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I fight like hell to pay as
little as possible
for two reasons.

24:39.078 --> 24:40.045 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Number one, I'm a businessman.

24:40.079 --> 24:42.481 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's the way you're
supposed to do it.

24:42.514 --> 24:44.817 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Now to
perspective.

24:44.850 --> 24:47.953 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How unusual is Trump's refusal
to release?

24:47.986 --> 24:50.389 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
In modern politics, he is alone.

24:50.422 --> 24:56.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since 1980, every president from
Ronald Reagan
to Barack Obama has released
their returns

24:56.061 --> 24:57.029 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
publicly.

24:57.062 --> 24:58.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And so has each nominee.

24:58.530 --> 25:01.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
John McCain released the fewest,
two years
of returns.

25:01.967 --> 25:06.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hillary Clinton has released the
most, 39
years of returns.

25:06.071 --> 25:08.340 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But was anyone else under audit?

25:08.374 --> 25:10.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Yes, Richard Nixon.

25:10.175 --> 25:12.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD NIXON, Former President
of the United
States: People have got to know
whether or

25:12.211 --> 25:14.012 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not their president is a crook.

25:14.046 --> 25:15.481 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Well, I'm not a crook.

25:15.514 --> 25:19.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Nixon wasn't
talking about
Watergate there.

25:19.184 --> 25:24.857 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He was talking about his
finances after an
IRS audit in 1973 showed he owed
more than

25:24.890 --> 25:27.860 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
$400,000 in back taxes.

25:27.893 --> 25:33.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nixon eventually released four
years of returns,
sparking the modern tradition.

25:33.265 --> 25:37.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Another option for Trump, like
fellow billionaire
politician Michael Bloomberg,
Trump could

25:37.803 --> 25:41.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
release a summary, or the first
pages of his
taxes.

25:41.407 --> 25:47.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Or he could he release the taxes
that have
completed audits, those up to
the year 2008.

25:47.646 --> 25:49.014 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
His response?

25:49.047 --> 25:50.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: The only one that
cares is the
press, I will tell you.

25:50.249 --> 25:52.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And even the press, I tell you,
it's not a
big deal.

25:52.184 --> 25:53.385 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
QUESTION: You don't think there
are voters
out there who...

25:53.419 --> 25:54.386 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: I don't think so,
no.

25:54.420 --> 25:55.854 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think people don't care.

25:55.888 --> 25:58.524 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But is that
true?

25:58.557 --> 26:03.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Actually, a recent poll found
two-thirds of
likely voters think seeing
candidates' tax

26:03.862 --> 26:05.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
returns is important.

26:05.531 --> 26:10.068 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And, in this election,
two-thirds of voters
don't agree on much.

26:10.102 --> 26:12.171 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Lisa
Desjardins.

26:12.204 --> 26:16.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Donald Trump's
tax returns
aren't the only way to gain
insight into his

26:16.975 --> 26:18.577 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
